results.occurrenceRemarks: A medium-small (<25 cm) but active bird, behaving similar to an Indian Robin, bouncing among the boulders at the base of a cliff. Identifiable as a male Mocking Cliff-Chat by its coloration and behaviour, and as sub-species bamabarae by its location a short distance to the northeast of the Mandingo Mountains and lack of a prominent white cap
